HEADWORD: Incognizance
<hw>In*cog"ni*zance</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Failure to
cognize, apprehended, or notice.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>This <qex>incognizance</qex> may be explained.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
Hamilton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Incognizant</ent>⟦br⟧
